<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Elixia</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-23 13:56:58</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I stop by and knock off the Goblins every time I leave Halas and head to BlackBurrow or Qeynos. I guess I have been lucky because I now have the Gavel of Justice, lots off EXP, and quite a few pp from those mobs. I tried camping too (for many hours), not worth it. Easier to make a quick stop there every time you pass by...not too far out of the way. BTW, my cracked staff gives a better whack than the Gavel does, but the gavel does add a few manna. Make sure you SLAM the caster to interrupt his casting, then he is easy to kill if you are 7+ level. And, he does spawn outside the igloo also. I nailed him 3 time outside, the rest were inside the 2nd igloo</font></td></tr></table>
